Popular Juju music singer Dayo Kujore is dead. The musician died yesterday, about 84 days to his 64th birthday on April 4, 2022. Sources in the home of the musician first announced the demise of the “Soko” exponent while his widow and daughters confirmed the development to journalists without giving details. The Nation gathered that the singer was confirmed dead at the Lagos State University Teach Hospital (LASUTH) in Ikeja, Lagos. - Advertisement - Entertainers and entertainment practitioners have continued to express shock at the singer’s death.   JAMB to tertiary institutions: conclude 2021 admissions     Court sentences man to death by hanging in Ibadan     Kidnappers of former Taraba SSG’s children, others demand…   Two of his daughters – Ayinke and Kenny – confirmed the death of their father and eulogised him. Kenny, a rising Nollywood actress, who began her career in the reality talent show, “Next Movie Star”, expressed sadness over her dad’s death. Ayinke, an on-air personality (OAP), said it’s a sad time for the family. But she’s added that her father led a good and fulfilled life. Sola Fajobi, the brain behind “The Next Movie Star”, expressed sadness over the death of the singer, saying: “So sad. Wonder Dayo Kujore played for us last November at Pose Nite Club. We both sang to one of his hits as I joined him on the bandstand. He was vibrant and entertaining. May his soul rest in peace.” Filmmaker Kabat Esosa Egbon said: “This is sad. May his soul rest in peace.” Fuji singer Kolade Onanuga said: “May Allah forgive the late Dayo Kujore for his sins and grant him eternal rest.”